                <h1>Barack Obama begins another term with another call for national unity</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/8edc8b2f-05f6-44a8-9fe4-cf25e5dd90bc.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="Beyonce&#x20;sings&#x20;the&#x20;National&#x20;Anthem&#x20;during&#x20;the&#x20;Inauguration&#x20;Ceremony&#x20;of&#x20;President&#x20;Barack&#x20;Obama&#x20;after&#x20;he&#x20;is&#x20;sworn&#x20;in&#x20;for&#x20;a&#x20;second&#x20;term&#x20;at&#x20;the&#x20;United&#x20;States&#x20;Capitol&#x20;in&#x20;Washington&#x20;on&#x20;Jan.&#x20;21.&#x20;Stand-alone&#x20;photo&#x20;INAUG.&#x20;Moved&#x20;Monday,&#x20;Jan.&#x20;21,&#x20;2013.&#x20;&#x28;MUST&#x20;CREDIT&#x3A;&#x20;Washington&#x20;Post&#x20;photo&#x20;by&#x20;Marvin&#x20;Joseph&#x29;" class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            Beyonce sings the National Anthem during the Inauguration Ceremony of President Barack Obama after he is sworn in for a second term at the United States Capitol in Washington on Jan. 21. Stand-alone photo INAUG. Moved Monday, Jan. 21, 2013. (MUST CREDIT: Washington Post photo by Marvin Joseph)

                            
